BSkyB rises to new record on short squeeze . Shares in BSkyB climbed to another record peak on Monday on what traders characterized as a short squeeze . By 0858 GMT , the shares were up 9p to 659p , after rising as high as 661p earlier . They have jumped by about 15 percent during the last three weeks , with the rise accelerating after the shares broke through 600p . " I think the market is just short of stock , " said one market maker of the recent advance in the shares . - - Debra Sherman , London Newsroom + 44 171 542 4026 
